  "conditions": "6 AM- Dark clouds and driving winds can't contain the stoke invoked by a Saturday on the slopes. In fact, the wild weather will only amplify the vibe as a gentle morning flurry becomes a plastering afternoon onslaught that cannot be denied. Warm temperatures in the low elevations will allow a little liquid to fall, as highs hang in the upper 20s at the summit and the mid-40s in Teton Village. Aggressive west winds in the 15 to 50 mph range will energize your soul as they contour the ridgelines and flatten the bowl. Stormy mountains often lead to moments of excessive excitability. But, emerging from the chaos, you somehow always find satisfaction and tranquility. -Lege",
